{
  "stem": "1858.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 418.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And-- but our home was never the same again.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Instead of songs, it was still.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was quiet.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a sad place.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "It was nothing like the home that I remembered from before.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 59,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--were passed upon us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It started with the white armband with the Star of David on it.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then it was changed to a yellow star with the word Jude-- the Jew-- on the front and on the back of your clothing.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We were barred from certain sections of the city.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We were forbidden to enter a theater or a movie house.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We could not travel on a train or a streetcar.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You see, what was happening, it was happening very gradually, very systematically.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And we were being conditioned.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But slowly, our liberties were being taken away from us one at a time.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And with each of the liberties that we gave up, we thought-- or hoped-- that perhaps now they will leave us alone.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Soon, Jewish property was being confiscated, and so on.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because who could possibly, possibly have imagined or believed that things will get that much worse to the extent-- you see, the Nazis had a way of deceiving us.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They deceived us all the way to the gas chambers.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I cannot possibly imagine today that if somebody would have come and told us that there is such a plan that anyone would even have believed it, that it was possible.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Because this is inconceivable until today, to believe that highly cultural nation can carry out such horrendous crimes.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "In December of 1939, I was in school, and I was a happy child.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We-- the school-- the building that I was going to school to was a brand new.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "They were building it in 1938.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 60,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "It was a beautiful building.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
